## Quick Start

Lobu boots as a single Node process. Bring your own Postgres (managed instance or local — `brew services start postgresql` works for dev) and point `.env` at it.

```bash
# 1. Edit .env and set DATABASE_URL

# 2. Boot Lobu (gateway + workers + memory backend in one Node process)
npx @lobu/cli@latest run

# 3. Stop with Ctrl+C
```

Logs go to stdout — pipe to your supervisor of choice (`pm2`, `systemd`, etc.) for production.

## Upgrading to Latest Version

Pull the latest CLI to pick up gateway + worker improvements:

```bash
# The CLI ships the embedded backend it boots, so updating the CLI
# updates Lobu itself. No image pull, no compose restart.
npx @lobu/cli@latest run
```

Compare your `.env` with the latest `.env.example` in the [Lobu repo](https://github.com/lobu-ai/lobu) when upgrading and add any new required variables.

## Configuration

### Environment Variables

Edit `.env` to configure:

- `DATABASE_URL` — Postgres connection string (with pgvector)
- `PUBLIC_GATEWAY_URL` — Public URL for OAuth callbacks
- `WORKER_ALLOWED_DOMAINS` — Allowed domains for worker network access

### Platform Connections

Platforms (Slack, Telegram, Discord, WhatsApp, Teams) are configured through the gateway APIs — no per-platform env vars are required in `.env`. Manage connections against `{PUBLIC_GATEWAY_URL}/api/v1/connections` and related auth/config endpoints.

### Worker Customization

Worker behavior is controlled by:

- `[agents.<id>.skills]` blocks in `lobu.toml` — declare MCP servers, OAuth, and tool policy.
- `nixPackages` per agent — pulls binaries onto the worker's `PATH` via `nix-shell`. The worker uses [just-bash](https://github.com/nicholasgasior/just-bash) to wrap shell commands; interpreters and package managers are excluded from the allowlist by default. Set `LOBU_ALLOW_UNSANDBOXED_EXEC=1` per-agent to opt back in if you genuinely need them.

